This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it addresses the problem of image dehazing using convolutional neural networks. The use of a bilinear composition loss function also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories as it deals with image processing and enhancement.
